snippet: The man in western China was the 134th person to self-immolate in protest of Chinese rule over Tibetan areas, Radio Free Asia reported.
abstract: Tibetan man sets himself on fire and dies outside police station in Gansu Province, China; man is reportedly 134th person to have self-immolated in protest of Chinese control over Tibetan areas.
lead_paragraph: The man in western China was the 134th person to self-immolate in protest of Chinese rule over Tibetan areas, Radio Free Asia reported.

headline.main: Tibetan Man Dies After Self-Immolation in Protest of Chinese Rule
